On an individual basis that's exactly what they do, but collectively they represent an extraordinary explosion of design – overlapping ideas developed in isolation and crowded into a single, screaming set of options. Pick any one of Seasons, Ultimate Team or Career Mode and you could happily lose yourself for 12 months, but the game does a scrappy job of preparing you for what might be a year-long journey, with barely any explanation of which you might enjoy most, or how they sit in relation to one another.
